    <p><strong>Video Reserves:</strong> A new tool has been made available to your Sakai course called <strong>Video Reserves</strong>. You can add this feature to your course through the Sakai Site Editor, go to the Edit Tools, and select Video Reserves. Save your tool selections, and the tool appear on the left navigation bar.</p>
    <p><strong>All other reserves:</strong> Once your reserves are prepared, you will be given a direct link to your course reserves in the old reserves system. You can add a generic <strong>Web Content</strong> tool to your course and paste the direct link there so that your students can easily access your reserves list from within Sakai. This will include all reserves except streaming video. Please remember that we will be transitioning to the new unified reserves system following Fall Break 2013. After that, you will have access to a single tool in Sakai called <strong>Library Reserves</strong> which will include all of your course reserves.</p>
    <p><strong>Questions?</strong> Please contact the library or the OIT Help Desk (<a href="mailto:oithelp@nd.edu">oithelp@nd.edu</a>) if you have any questions about reserves or how to access them within Sakai.</p>
  </div>
